{"title_page": "Jerediah Horsford", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Jerediah Horsford\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| assembly = New York State\n| constituency_AM = [[Livingston County, New York|Livingston County]]\n| term_start = 1831\n| term_end = 1831\n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| state2 = [[New York (state)|New York]]\n| district2 = [[New York's 29th congressional district|29th]]\n| term_start2 = March 4, 1851\n| term_end2 = March 3, 1853\n| predecessor2 = [[Robert L. Rose]]\n| successor2 = [[Azariah Boody]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1791|3|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Charlotte, Vermont]], U.S.\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1875|1|14|1791|3|8}}\n| death_place = [[Livonia, New York]], U.S.\n| resting_place = Moscow Cemetery, now in [[Leicester (village), New York|Leicester, New York]], U.S.\n| party = {{unbulleted list| [[Anti-Masonic Party|Anti-Masonic]] (1831) | [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] (1851-1853)}}\n| children = [[Eben Norton Horsford]]\n}}\n\n'''Jerediah Horsford''' (March 8, 1791 \u2013 January 14, 1875) was an American politician from [[New York (state)|New York]].\n\n==Life==\nHorsford attended the common schools, and then engaged in agricultural pursuits. He served during the [[War of 1812]], took part in the defense of [[Burlington, Vermont]]. He later moved to [[Genesee County, New York]], where he served as an officer in a unit which took part in the [[Battle of Lundy's Lane]].\n\nIn 1815, he went to [[Moscow, New York]] as a missionary to the [[Seneca Indians]]. In 1818 he moved to [[Mount Morris, New York]], where he was a farmer. He was a pioneer in scientific farming methods, an active member of several agricultural societies, and the inventor of an animal feed named ''Horsford's Cattle Food''.\n\nHe remained in the New York Militia, and rose to colonel and commander of the regiment based in [[Livingston County, New York|Livingston County]].\n\nHe was an [[Anti-Masonic Party|Anti-Masonic]] member of the [[New York State Assembly]] (Livingston Co.) in [[54th New York State Legislature|1831]].\n\nHorsford was elected as a [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] to the [[32nd United States Congress]], holding office from March 4, 1851, to March 3, 1853.\n\nHe moved to [[Livonia, New York]] in 1863. He died in Livonia and was buried at Moscow Cemetery, now in [[Leicester (village), New York|Leicester, New York]].\n\nHis children included inventor and scientist [[Eben Norton Horsford]].\n\n==Sources==\n{{CongBio|H000796}}\n*{{Findagrave|7742624}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{US House succession box\n| state=New York\n| district=29\n| before=[[Robert L. Rose]]\n| after=[[Azariah Boody]]\n| years=1851\u20131853}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Horsford, Jerediah}}\n[[Category:1791 births]]\n[[Category:1875 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Whigs]]\n[[Category:Anti-Masonic Party politicians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Members of the New York State Assembly]]\n[[Category:People from Charlotte, Vermont]]\n[[Category:People from Leicester, New York]]\n[[Category:American militiamen in the War of 1812]]\n[[Category:Whig Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:19th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Livonia, New York]]\n[[Category:American militia officers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Jerediah Horsford\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| assembly = New York State\n| constituency_AM = [[Livingston County, New York|Livingston County]]\n| term_start = 1831\n| term_end = 1831\n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| state2 = [[New York (state)|New York]]\n| district2 = [[New York's 29th congressional district|29th]]\n| term_start2 = March 4, 1851\n| term_end2 = March 3, 1853\n| predecessor2 = [[Robert L. Rose]]\n| successor2 = [[Azariah Boody]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1791|3|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Charlotte, Vermont]], U.S.\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1875|1|14|1791|3|8}}\n| death_place = [[Livonia, New York]], U.S.\n| resting_place = Moscow Cemetery, now in [[Leicester (village), New York|Leicester, New York]], U.S.\n| party = {{unbulleted list| [[Anti-Masonic Party|Anti-Masonic]] (1831) | [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] (1851-1853)}}\n| children = [[Eben Norton Horsford]]\n}}\n'''Jerediah Horsford''' (March 8, 1791 in [[Charlotte, Vermont|Charlotte]], [[Chittenden County, Vermont]] \u2013 January 14, 1875 in [[Livonia (town), New York|Livonia]], [[Livingston County, New York]]) was an American politician from [[New York (state)|New York]].\n\n==Life==\nHorsford attended the common schools, and then engaged in agricultural pursuits. He served during the [[War of 1812]], took part in the defense of [[Burlington, Vermont]]. He later moved to [[Genesee County, New York]], where he served as an officer in a unit which took part in the [[Battle of Lundy's Lane]].\n\nIn 1815, he went to [[Moscow, New York]] as a missionary to the [[Seneca Indians]]. In 1818 he moved to [[Mount Morris, New York]], where he was a farmer. He was a pioneer in scientific farming methods, an active member of several agricultural societies, and the inventor of an animal feed named ''Horsford's Cattle Food''.\n\nHe remained in the New York Militia, and rose to colonel and commander of the regiment based in [[Livingston County, New York|Livingston County]].\n\nHe was an [[Anti-Masonic Party|Anti-Masonic]] member of the [[New York State Assembly]] (Livingston Co.) in [[54th New York State Legislature|1831]].\n\nHorsford was elected as a [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] to the [[32nd United States Congress]], holding office from March 4, 1851, to March 3, 1853.\n\nHe moved to [[Livonia, New York]] in 1863. He died in Livonia and was buried at Moscow Cemetery, now in [[Leicester (village), New York|Leicester, New York]].\n\nHis children included inventor and scientist [[Eben Norton Horsford]].\n\n==Sources==\n{{CongBio|H000796}}\n*{{Findagrave|7742624}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{US House succession box\n| state=New York\n| district=29\n| before=[[Robert L. Rose]]\n| after=[[Azariah Boody]]\n| years=1851\u20131853}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Horsford, Jerediah}}\n[[Category:1791 births]]\n[[Category:1875 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Whigs]]\n[[Category:Anti-Masonic Party politicians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Members of the New York State Assembly]]\n[[Category:People from Charlotte, Vermont]]\n[[Category:People from Leicester, New York]]\n[[Category:American militiamen in the War of 1812]]\n[[Category:Whig Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:19th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Livonia, New York]]\n[[Category:American militia officers]]\n", "name_user": "Billybob2002", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerediah_Horsford"}
