{"title_page": "Ink Master (season 13)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television season\n| bgcolour             = #40E0D0\n| country              = United States\n| num_episodes         = 15\n| network              = [[Paramount Network]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2020|1|07}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2020|04|14}}\n| module1              = {{Infobox reality competition season\n| host                 = [[Dave Navarro]]\n| judges               = {{Plainlist|\n*Oliver Peck\n*[[Chris Nunez]]\n}}\n| num_contestants      = 20\n| winner               = None\n}}\n| prev_season          = [[Ink Master (season 12)|Season 12]]\n}}\n\n'''''Ink Master: Turf War''''' is the thirteenth season of the tattoo reality competition ''[[Ink Master]]'' that premiered on [[Paramount Network]] on January 7 and ended on April 14, 2020 with a total of fifteen episodes instead of sixteen due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] that caused the live finale that was going to air on April 21 to be scrapped.<ref name=\"finale\">{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/inkmaster/status/1250257939341938688?s=19|title=Ink Master Statement on Finale|publisher=twitter.com|author=Ink Master|date=2020-04-14|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref name=\"spike\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.inkedmag.com/original-news/inkmaster-season13-castannouncement|title=Meet the Cast of Ink Master Season 13|publisher= [[Inked Magazine]]|accessdate=November 17, 2019|date=November 12, 2019}}</ref> Host [[Dave Navarro]] and [[Chris Nunez]] both returned as co-judges. Oliver Peck made his last season appearance as co-judge at the time controversy erupted with old photos of him wearing blackface makeup from his previous MySpace page being leaked online.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/ink-master-oliver-peck-leaving-blackface-controversy/|title='Appalled' Ink Master and Oliver Peck Part Ways After Blackface Controversy|publisher= TV Line|author=Matt Webb Mitovich|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=January 7, 2020}}</ref> \n\nSeason 13 introduced 20 artists that were split into four teams based on their respective home region with each region being lead by an ''Ink Master'' veteran: Jason Elliott and Frank Ready from [[Ink Master (season 10)|season 10]], and Jimmy Snaz and Angel Rose from [[Ink Master (season 11)|season 11]]. This season is the first season in ''Ink Master'' history to not declare a winner. The three finalists - Bob Jones, Angel Rose and Jimmy Snaz - each received a share of the monetary prize, and their finished back and chest tattoos were revealed on ''Ink Master'''s social media platforms.<ref name=\"finale\" />\n\n==Judging and ranking==\n''The judge listing types are:''\n\n*'''Judging Panel'''\n::The judging panel is a table of three or more primary judges in addition to the coaches. The judges make their final decision by voting to see who had best tattoo of the day, and who goes home. In episode 7, Dave Navarro offers Jason Elliott a pardon so he may return to the competition. The following week in episode 9, Dave tells the artists that both Chris and Oliver each have one pardon they may offer to any eliminated artist of their choosing.\n\n==Contestants==\n===East===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Contestants\n!Years\nExperience\n! Hometown\n|-\n| Jessa Bigelow\n|6\n| [[Harrison, New Jersey]]\n|-\n| Emac\n|8\n| [[Baltimore, Maryland]]\n|-\n| Andrew Hicks\n|7\n| [[New York, New York]]\n|-\n| K Lenore Siner\n|3\n| [[Salem, Massachusetts]]\n|-\n| Jimmy Snaz<br/><small>''[[Ink Master (season 11)|Grudge Match \u2013 Cleen vs. Christian]]''</small>\n|13\n|[[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n|}\n\n===South===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Contestants\n!Years\nExperience\n! Hometown\n|-\n| Nychelle Elise\n|6\n| [[Plano, Texas]]\n|-\n| Jason Elliott<br/><small>''[[Ink Master (season 10)|Return of the Masters]]''</small>\n|6\n| [[College Station, Texas]]\n|-\n| Patrick Flynn\n|18\n| [[Asheville, North Carolina]]\n|-\n| Jordi Pla\n|5\n|[[Miami, Florida]]